docs.abstract: The airplane maker will pay penalties in France, Britain and the United States, removing a legal hurdle as it competes with its rival Boeing.
docs.snippet: The airplane maker will pay penalties in France, Britain and the United States, removing a legal hurdle as it competes with its rival Boeing.
docs.lead_paragraph: PARIS — Airbus will pay $4 billion in fines to settle a lengthy global corruption investigation, a French court announced Friday, removing a legal cloud over the world’s largest plane maker as it seeks to keep ahead of its rival Boeing after the grounding of Boeing’s 737 Max plane.

headline.main: Airbus to Pay $4 Billion to Settle Corruption Inquiry
headline.print_headline: Airbus to Pay Steep Penalty To End Case

docs.abstract: Students at the University of the South sought more transparency and sustainability. Were they too polite?
docs.snippet: Students at the University of the South sought more transparency and sustainability. Were they too polite?
docs.lead_paragraph: SEWANEE, Tenn. — In 2013, the Board of Regents at the University of the South endorsed a sustainability plan. The school pledged, among many other things, to disclose its endowment holdings and initiate a communitywide discussion about whether those investments matched its values and commitment to the environment.

headline.main: Why It’s So Hard to Make an Endowment More Socially Responsible
headline.print_headline: More Green Endowment? It’s Not Easy
